This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with improving object detection in images. Additionally, the use of spatial relations between objects and the analysis of contextual object detection problem are common topics in computer vision research. The paper also utilizes a probabilistic model, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of probabilistic models and the analysis of contextual inference also suggest that it may belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the difficulty of learning when the context and detector strongly disagree, which suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
